\epsilon- \delta
 \displaystyle \lim_{x \to  -4} \frac { x^2 +  6x + 8 }{x + 4}  = - 2 
\delta \leq 1
 | x + 4 | < 1 
x < -1 
 \left| \dfrac { x^2 +  6x + 8 }{x + 4} + 2 \right| = \left| \dfrac { x^2 + 8x + 16}{x + 4}\right| < \left| \dfrac { x^2 + 8x + 16}{x}\right| < |x^2 + 8x + 16| = |(x+4)^2| = (x+4)^2 \ .   
(x+4)^2 < \epsilon
 | x + 4 | < \sqrt \epsilon 
\delta = \min \{1, \sqrt \epsilon  \}
x^2 + 6x + 8 = (x+2)(x + 4).
